
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gamma4scanimage` baraye ta'yin meghdare gamma baraye scan image az dastgahhaye scanner estefade mishavad. Gamma balance rangha ro rooye scan ta'sir mizare va ba in dastoor mitavan an ra behtar kard.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--gamma float`  --> 🌈 Ta'yin meghdare gamma. Meghdar bayad yek adad ashaar dar rangeh mored nazar bashad.
    🔹 `--red float`   --> ❤️ Ta'yin meghdare gamma baraye rang ghermez.
    🔹 `--green float` --> 💚 Ta'yin meghdare gamma baraye rang sabz.
    🔹 `--blue float`  --> 💙 Ta'yin meghdare gamma baraye rang abi.
    🔹 `--help`        --> ℹ️ Namayesh rahnama va etela'at estefade.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gamma4scanimage --gamma 2.2

    🔹 Ta'yin meghdare gamma baraye hameye rangha be 2.2

    $ gamma4scanimage --red 1.8 --green 2.0 --blue 2.2

    🔹 Ta'yin meghdare gamma joda baraye ranghaye ghermez, sabz va abi.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gamma4scanimage --gamma 1.0

    🔹 Ta'yin meghdare gamma baraye hameye rangha be 1.0. In meghdar hich taghiri dar rangha ijad nemikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gamma4scanimage` command is used to set the gamma value for scanning images from scanner devices. Gamma affects the color balance on the scan, and this command helps to improve it.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--gamma float`  --> 🌈 Sets the gamma value. The value should be a decimal number within the acceptable range.
    🔹 `--red float`   --> ❤️ Sets the gamma value for the red color.
    🔹 `--green float` --> 💚 Sets the gamma value for the green color.
    🔹 `--blue float`  --> 💙 Sets the gamma value for the blue color.
    🔹 `--help`        --> ℹ️ Displays help information and usage instructions.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gamma4scanimage --gamma 2.2

    🔹 Sets the gamma value for all colors to 2.2

    $ gamma4scanimage --red 1.8 --green 2.0 --blue 2.2

    🔹 Sets the gamma values separately for the red, green, and blue colors.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gamma4scanimage --gamma 1.0

    🔹 Sets the gamma value for all colors to 1.0. This value does not make any changes in colors.
